Hungary’s OTP Bank Gains, Erasing Loss, as European Stocks Rise

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-10-10T14:16:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/hungary-s-otp-bank-gains-erasing-loss-as-european-stocks-rise.html
OTP Bank Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest
lender, erased earlier losses as European stocks advanced.  OTP’s shares rallied 1.8 percent to 3,210 forint as of 4:08
p.m. in Budapest, after dropping as much as 3.3 percent earlier
today. The benchmark BUX index, in which OTP has a 27 percent
weighting, gained 2.4 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  